<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4c.11.44"/>
<note type="curatorial">1. Mott Collecton U of Mo
Library</note>
<note type="clerical">[1926]</note>
<opener> <dateline>July 26.</dateline>
<salute>Dear Mott:</salute> </opener>
<p>I've just seen your review of P.V. in The Sat.
Rev. of Lit. <hi rend="underline">Bully</hi>! You
certainly did it generously and I'm grateful. That
will help a lot.</p>

<p>You'll be glad to hear that my stuff shows a
very considerable increase in sales this year. <hi
rend="underline">Indian Wars</hi> went into a new
edition in March - making three, counting the de
luxe. The school edition of Friends-Glass <fw
type="curatorial">44</fw> <fw type="authorial"
>-2-</fw> made the biggest advance yet. I'm
greatly encouraged.</p>

<p>When are you going to take a vacation here in
these beautiful hills with us? You are, of course,
invited - <hi rend="underline">you</hi> meaning
the family too. I have a car &amp; could show you
around.</p>
<closer> <salute>Kindest thoughts!</salute>
<signed>Jno. Neihardt</signed> </closer>
</div1>
